		"name": "Task Management API",
		"description": "RESTful API for task management with user authentication built with Node.js, Express.js, and MongoDB.\n\n## Features\n- User registration and login\n- JWT-based authentication\n- Complete Task CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)\n\n## Tech Stack\n- Node.js\n- Express.js\n- MongoDB\n- Mongoose\n- JWT (JSON Web Tokens)\n- bcryptjs\n\n## Authentication Flow\n1. Register a new user via `/auth/register`\n2. Login with credentials via `/auth/login` to receive JWT token\n3. Use the token in Authorization header for all task operations\n\n## Error Responses\n- **400** - Bad Request (Invalid input data)\n- **401** - Unauthorized (Missing or invalid token)\n- **404** - Not Found (Resource not found)\n- **500** - Server Error (Internal server error)",
